                <h4 data-uuid="cd7c5083d71a44f898972427df8f3765">Main Idea</h4>
                <p class="main-idea" data-uuid="a96567b2e94e4388822ad4cf9f0057f8">Jimmy Carter was elected president in 1976.</p>
                <h2 data-uuid="df9a6ebae1c94a9d955d7dca572fbbbf">Carter
                    Elected</h2>
                <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="6c5ec733e79646ebb15369d37ef8cd32"></div>
            </article>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="d04f3970a0d049b7948db9bc3af5b094">To oppose Republican Gerald Ford in the 1976
            presidential election, Democrats nominated <b><dfn title="Carter, Jimmy">Jimmy
            Carter</dfn></b>, a little-known former governor of Georgia. The Democrats
            purposely chose a candidate who was untouched by recent government scandals.
            Carter knew that the Vietnam War and Watergate had badly shaken American
            voters’ trust in government. “I will never lie to you,” he told voters.<br />
        </p>
