        <p data-uuid="5a8f2c00eca948fe92d2ec65b17d2a20">Carter also wanted to expand the use of nuclear
            power. This was one way he hoped to decrease the country’s dependence on
            imported oil. But an accident at the Three Mile Island nuclear power plant in
            Pennsylvania caused new worries about the safety of nuclear energy. On March
            28, 1979, a reactor core at Three Mile Island overheated. As a result, the
            plant released a small amount of radioactive gas into the air. This frightening
            incident damaged the nuclear power industry, and the federal government put in
            place a ban on building new reactors.<br />
        </p>
